    %h2(style = "margin-top:0") What is Infinispan ?
    %p.lead
      Infinispan is a distributed in-memory key/value data store with optional schema, available under the 
      Apache License 2.0. It can be used both as an embedded Java library and as a language-independent service 
      accessed remotely over a variety of protocols (HotRod, REST, Memcached and WebSockets). It offers advanced 
      functionality such as transactions, events, querying and distributed processing.
      %a(href = "/features") Read about our features
